</section>
<section id="fs-idm277768528" class="section-summary">
<list id="fs-idm258568000" list-type="enumerated">
<item>What are the differences between values-based ethics and compliance in organizations?</item>
</list>
<para id="fs-idm217871984">A compliance-based ethical approach is simple and direct. It provides a basic integrity to the participant since it is spelled out in clear terms. If the individual or organization exhibits destructive behaviors, their rights can be restricted. An integrity-based ethics code fills the receiver with demands based on the highest expectations.</para>
</section>
